Rating: 3
I had the same problem as Los Angeles with the chocolate chips melting, but not becoming liquid enough to dip the strawberries in. I melted the chips in the double boiler as instructed with the vegetable shortening. Not wanting to throw out the lump of chocolate (or worse eat it) I added some low fat milk in small quantities until the mixture became smooth and liquid. After that, they turned out great. Maybe some chocolate chips have less oil than others?

Rating: 3
I made these without the sprinkles, since I didn't have them in the pantry. So as not to get my whole hand in the "chocolate pot" when dipping, I used a soup ladle to retrieve the melted chocolate and then dipped the strawberry into that. Also I let the dipped strawberries dry upside down (stem down) in mini muffin tins, and then put them in the refrigerator. This way, one side wasn't flattened.

