Rating: 4
I paired this with the Fresh Fruit with Creamy Gran Marnier Sauce (on this site) for a party buffet. Easy, elegant, delicious! There certainly were no worries about the strawberries breaking down, that plate was EMPTY when I left the party. It also was quite lovely for individual servings with a couple of strawberries nestled on the cream in a small ramekin. To the Cook on 4/16/01, don't "dip" the strawberries in the sprinkles (or whatever topping you are using), "sprinkle" the sprinkles, and then only on one side. That way, you can control the amount of coating the strawberries get and they don't come out so thick.

